'''''Star Wars Insider'' 42''' is the forty-second issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was published in [[February]] [[1999]].

==Contents==
===Features===
*"[[THX: The Sound And The Fury]]" {{C|by [[Kevin Fitzpatrick]]}}
*:<small>[[Kevin Fitzpatrick]] offers a preview of the new sound system developed by THX and Dolby to premiere with [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|''The Phantom Menace'']]&ndash; Dolby Digital-Surround EX.</small>
*"[[Darth Maul: Evil Has a New Name]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>He's scary, he's tough, and he's a Wu Shu master. [[Scott Chernoff]] meets [[Ray Park]], the actor behind the make-up and double-sided lightsaber of ''Episode I'' villain [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth]] [[Maul]].</small>
*"[[George Lucas Down Under]]"
*:<small>Our favorite director talks about [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Episodes II'']] and [[Star Wars: Episode III Revenge of the Sith|''III'']] at his press conference Down Under&ndash;and the ''Insider'' is there to hear it.</small>
*"[[Frank Oz: Blizzard of Oz]]" {{C|by Scott Chernoff}}
*:<small>The multi-talented director/performer who brought [[Yoda/Legends|Yoda]] to life is back for Episode I. Frank Oz talks to Scott Chernoff about directing, ''the Muppets'', and the triumphant return of the Jedi Master.</small>

